anentrypoint-design app-shell jank root cause + fix (2026-05-28): .app-main is a height:100% flex column (app-shell.css:283-292); the rule .app-main > *{min-height:0} (line 293) combined with children's default flex-shrink:1 compressed every direct child BELOW its content height whenever total content exceeded the fixed-height scroll container - collapsing the hero h1 box to ~13px while glyphs painted at ~81px, jamming the .cli quickstart block, across every page and every consumer. FIX: .app-main > *{flex-shrink:0} with .chat/.ds-file-stage/.grow kept flex-shrink:1 (the intended growable children). Diagnosed via the live page as debugger: Range.getClientRects showed glyph h81 vs box h13, immune to height/line-height/display overrides, fixed only by stopping the flex compression. The gm site also had two independent bugs: font link loaded Archivo Black+Instrument Serif (never used) instead of Space Grotesk (the actual --ff token), and the flatspace-rendered /paper/ route never ran mermaid (docs/paper.html startOnLoad:true fires before article injection) - fixed by dynamic-import mermaid + run({nodes}) after host.innerHTML in site/theme.mjs, and active-nav matched by full-path startsWith which broke under the /gm/ base path (fixed to match last path segment).